<paragraph id="8BFB8D73AC116143FF28F031B497FC7F" blockId="8.[151,1437,840,1332]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Distinctive of this species are female dorsal opisthosomal setae which are set on tubercles, spiculate, do not taper, shorter than distances to next row of setae. Fourth pair of dorsocentrals (f 
<number id="3D8C9F54AC116143FBE8F007B27BFC41" box="[1111,1119,894,908]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
) nearer to each other than members of other three pairs of dorsocentrals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
